On Tue, 17 May 2005, < Arnaud > wrote:

>I am a little scared of trying to get oil at 227 degrees on the gas
>stove in the kitchen. (smell, fire, wife ...)

I wouldn't worry about oil at that temp. I set my deep fat fryer
to 350-375deg when cooking food. Use cooking oil and closely monitor
the temp. You'll know if you're getting close to fire as the oil
will start smoking heavily when getting close to 400+ deg.

